# Template for a native Windows deployment. Copy to frontend\.env.local on
# the server BEFORE running `npm run build` — NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are
# baked into the compiled JS at build time, not read at runtime, so editing
# this file after building has no effect until you rebuild.
#
# REPLACE_WITH_SERVER_HOST must be the server's actual LAN/public hostname
# or IP (e.g. 192.168.1.50 or files.example.com) — not localhost. Every
# visitor's browser calls this URL directly (the API has no server-side
# proxy in front of it), so "localhost" would only ever work from the
# server's own browser.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://REPLACE_WITH_SERVER_HOST:8080
